<!--DOCTYPE section SYSTEM "file:/opt/share/xml/Oxygen/docbook/dtd/docbookx.dtd"--><ns3156:section xmlns:ns3156="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.networkServices.nfs.fileAccess">

  <ns3157:title xmlns:ns3157="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">File access in NFS</ns3157:title>
  <ns3158:para xmlns:ns3158="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      NFS provides a user on a client machine the same access as
      that same user on the server machine. The user and group
      ids (uid and gid) are sent along with each NFS RPC request.
  </ns3158:para>
  <ns3159:para xmlns:ns3159="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     This requires that the same uids and gids are used on the client 
     and  the  server  machine. 
  </ns3159:para>
  <ns3160:note xmlns:ns3160="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns3161:para xmlns:ns3161="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      A root user on a client machine should typically not get root file access
      to the server. This is squashed via the <ns3162:literal xmlns:ns3162="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">root_squash</ns3162:literal>
      option.
    </ns3161:para>
  </ns3160:note>
</ns3156:section>